How It All Works Together

Click Processing Pipeline

Request Arrives → nginx proxies to engine, sets X-Forwarded-For
Dynamic Blacklist Check → if IP in Redis set, 403 immediately
Static Blacklist Check → Bloom filter test against 12,000 IPs
Rate Limiter → fingerprint-based: 5 requests/second per fingerprint
Risk Score Accumulation (all checks run, none interrupt):

User-Agent check → +2 if suspicious
JS challenge check → +3 if missing/too fast/mismatch
Header heuristic → +2 if suspicious
Decision:

If riskScore >= 4: block with reason risk_score_exceeded
If riskScore < 4: allow with reason allowed
Asynchronous Actions:

Log to batch logger (PostgreSQL)
Increment dynamic blacklist counter if blocked
If counter reaches 5 in 1 hour → add IP to Redis blacklist
Response → {"status":"success"} or {"status":"flagged"}
Dynamic Blacklist Mechanism

text
Client request → riskScore >= 4 → increment counter(IP)
                                    ↓
                        counter == 5 in 1 hour? → SADD af:dynamic_blacklist IP
                                    ↓
                        All future requests from IP → 403
GeoIP Integration

text
Batch flush → for each log entry:
    if geoReader != nil → lookup country by IP → insert country
    else → insert empty country
