Instructions for My Colleague to Set Up GeoIP

Since I cannot download the GeoIP database, I have prepared the following instructions for my colleague in another country:

Setup Instructions

Download the GeoIP Database:

Visit https://www.maxmind.com/en/geolite2/signup
Create a free account
Download GeoLite2-Country.mmdb from https://www.maxmind.com/en/accounts/current/downloads/geoip
Add the Database to the Project:

bash
# From the project root:
mkdir -p geoip
cp ~/Downloads/GeoLite2-Country.mmdb geoip/
Uncomment the Volume in docker-compose.yml:

yaml
volumes:
  - ./deployments/blacklists/dirty_ips.txt:/app/data/dirty_ips.txt:ro
  - ./geoip/GeoLite2-Country.mmdb:/usr/share/GeoIP/GeoLite2-Country.mmdb:ro  # ← uncomment this line
Rebuild and Restart Engine:

bash
docker compose up -d --no-deps --build engine
Verify the Country Lookup:

bash
docker exec -it antifraud-postgres psql -U antifraud -d analytics -c "SELECT ip, country FROM click_logs ORDER BY processed_at DESC LIMIT 5;"
Should show two-letter country codes (e.g., US, DE, FR, RU).